===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|夂|口|ls=ic|t1=sole of foot}} – to come, to enter; original form of {{och-l|𢓜}} and {{och-l|格}}. The mouth could be referred to the entrance of a cavern or building (see [[高]], [[去]] and [[谷]]; however, this is not the case in [[向]]). Compare [[出]].

===Etymology===
{{der|zh|sit}}. Derived from {{och-l|舉|tr=kaʔ}} with distributive suffix ''-k''. Cognate with {{cog|tbq-lob-pro|*ka||all}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}})

